BD code how-to section expanded

BD code how-to

1) How to create new BD code

Product Owner (PO) is responsible to collect required information and submit the request to finance team. If the PO is not Manger rank or higher, please talk to OU head to ask someone to submit the creation request. 

  1. Read this page for BD code details, and identify the required information of the new BD code (Budget type, Decision tree, etc.)
  2. Ask the engagement partner to confirm the information is correct.
  3. Go to KIT BD project codes page and create new item. Make sure that Status is Creation Requested.
  4. After the new item is successfully created, Finance team create a new BD code record in IBS system.
  5. Finance team notifies to the PO when the requested BD code is available. Use the Teams channel JP - KIT-Finance / BD Code Requests (private channel)
  6. The new BD becomes effective after the engagement partner approves in IBS system, then Status of the list item goes to "Active".
  7. Optionally PO can use Charge start date filed to instruct project members from when they can start charging workhours to this BD code. Typically charge start date is the date of Start Gate event.


2) How to close BD code

When BD codes are no longer used (for instance releasing the product, end of life of the operating product), PO should close the BD code in order for project members to mischarge to unused BD codes.

  1. PO can use Charge end date filed to instruct project members until when they can charge workhours to this BD code. Typically charge end date is the date of Release Gate event.
  2. Go to KIT BD project codes page and locate the BD code to be closed. PO-filtered BD codes view helps you to show all BD codes assigned to you. Update Status to Closing Requested.
  3. Finance team notifies to the PO when the BD code is successfully closed. Use the Teams channel JP - KIT-Finance​​​​​​​ / BD Code Requests (private channel).


    3) How to rename/transfer existing BD code

    If PO finds misinformation in KIT BD project codes, do not hesitate to contact Finance team to correct information. The situation will include

    • The project name is changed
    • The project is moved to different program
    • PO is changed due to new assignment

    ​​​​​​​​​​​​​​
